Tottenham, Lazio Ease to Wins in Opening Games of Europa League Playoffs

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-08-18T22:04:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/tottenham-lazio-ease-to-wins-in-opening-games-of-europa-league-playoffs.html
Tottenham won 5-0 at Heart of
Midlothian and Lazio routed Rabotnicki 6-0 in the first games of
their Europa League soccer playoffs.  Rafael van der Vaart  scored after five minutes for
Tottenham last night in  Scotland , while Djibril Cisse scored
twice in Lazio’s home victory.  English clubs were unbeaten on the night. Fulham beat
Dnipro 3-0, Stoke won at Thun 1-0 and Birmingham tied 0-0 at
Nacional. Maribor beat Scottish champion Rangers 2-1 on Etien
Velikonja’s goal in stoppage time, while Celtic and Sion
finished scoreless in Glasgow.  Braga, last season’s runner-up to Porto, drew 0-0 at home
with  Young Boys . Atletico Madrid and PSG both won, while Roma
and Schalke lost.  The return matches in the two-game series will be played
Aug. 25. The 38 series winners advance the group stage of
 Europe ’s second-tier club competition, where they’re joined by
the 10 playoff losers from the elite  Champions League .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bob Bensch in  London  at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 